inline_comments.message:
why not just use Integer.parseInt?

a better option might be to declare a small nested static parameter class containing these two fields (with their default values) and then use the CODER.convert method to do the decoding:

  public static class Config {
    private int threadTimeout = 60;
    private int podStatusCheckInterval = 30;
  }

  var config = CODER.convert(getProperties(), Config.class)

no more need for string constants, Float.parse, etc.

Thanks Jim. Learnt about CODER.convert(). Have explored only decode/encode methods so far. This really simplified the task. 

private static ToscaServiceTemplate testControlLoopYamlSerialization(String controlLoopFilePath) {
        String controlLoopString = ResourceUtils.getResourceAsString(controlLoopFilePath);
        ToscaServiceTemplate serviceTemplate = yamlTranslator.fromYaml(controlLoopString, ToscaServiceTemplate.class);
        return serviceTemplate;
    }

